HEADWORD: Scaleback
<hw>Scale"back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous species of marine annelids of the family
<fam>Polynoidae</fam>, and allies, which have two rows of scales, or
elytra, along the back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

